MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2010-0036. Duncan v. Fifth Dist. Court of Appeals.

In Mandmaus and Procedendo. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus and procedendo. Upon consideration of relator’s application for dismissal,

It is ordered by the court that the application for dismissal is granted. Accordingly, this cause is dismissed.

Pfeifer, Acting C.J.
